The Enterprise and Innovation programme should serve entrepreneurs and companies to obtain resources in business innovation.
Companies should seek funding for the acquisition of new technologies, for industrial research and for the implementation of more effective organisational methods.
The Czech Republic is among the newly joined countries that are least likely to use EU funds.
