But during the hearing before U.S. District Judge Ewing Werlein Jr., each was convicted of conspiracy to defraud.
The three former executives of Greenwich Natwest, a unit of the Scottish group PLC in the Royal Bank, became a cause célèbre in Britain for the extradition proceedings that lasted two years.
In the United States, his case marks the loose end of an investigation launched after the collapse of Enron in 2001.
